<br>
Firstly, I do think it's easy to distinguish guilds I'd rather not be associated with due to posting history of members in places like the soapbox.  If a member of a guild has a history, for example, of flaming for flaming's sake then I'm willing to believe that their guild at least partially tolerates that sort of behavior internally.  In that regard, a member can reflect poorly on their guild.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I don't expect the converse to be true.  If someone's a highly-regarded poster, I don't necessarily expect their guild to be ideal.  At a minimum, they've done no harm, and I need more interaction with a guild before I can consider them worth associating with.<br>
<br>
Maybe this dynamic is why nobody ever &quot;wins&quot; in the soapbox.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=witherweaver>Witherweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 539<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/2/03 7:11:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=444.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Do you feel posters represent thier guilds?</span><hr size=1> Just because Thraall posts here does not mean that everyone in Fire and Fury has the writing aptitude of a 5 year old.<br>
